results.name: Multiplicative permutation of integers: a(n) = A234840(A235199(n)).
comment: Please see the comments at A234743. The observations given there apply also here.
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..378
Index entries for sequences that are permutations of the natural numbers
formula: Multiplicative with a(p_i) = p_{A235048(i)} for primes with index i, except for cases i=3 and i=4, use p_18 and p_8 (61 and 19) instead of 19 and 61. For the composites, the value is determined as: a(u*v) = a(u) * a(v).
xref: Inverse: A234743. Similarly composed multiplicative permutations, with more tractable cycle structures: A235485/A235486, A235493/A235494.
results.author: _Antti Karttunen_, Jan 04 2014
